choices.text:
coming up with ideas of things to do when I get home from school and all my classmates are rushing out of the house for social events. They eventually come home by around 9.00pm while I’m still left with a couple of hours before dinner, a big chunk of hours that are a real nightmare to fill.Help me to learn what I should do to make the best usage of my spare times.

Anna

To manage yourself and your time efficently, beard up on two important concepts that’s you are failing to recognize so far — time management and productivity. Their main difference:

Time management is a set of practices to help you increase the productivity of your time utilization while productivity is the number of times you consume work in a particular time frame.

For example, what you are currently doing is time management because you want to figure out how to make the best usage of your time when you eventually come home.

On the other hand, when you come home and you do something meaningful (Note: Everyday you must do something meaningful to enjoy and experience pleasure), you are free using your time productively.

To increase the productivity of your time utilization, you need to make a conscious effort to focus your mind on the thing you are doing while you do it and choose to just do that one thing, let other activities go and delay them *if* the activity you are doing requires your full attention. Stop checking social media or the news between other activities.

It’s really that simple but not easy due
